commit.message: changed project name in readme and created presentation markdown
scaled the canvas size and adjusted the timer
added time remaining for each emotion
added encrypted password.pdf and temp debug emotes from hack5
pass emo_number and emo_duration as floats to start_stream
added command line options to hack5
optimised model such that it records emotions for a given interval of time and then takes the most common emotion as the emotion displayed for that interval
fixed error in hashing in hack5.py
updates 'duration_of_emotion' to decimal instead of integer
moved password creation into a function
added unpassword-ed password txt file with password emotions included
Pair Programming on outputting emotions as array
